===Etymology===
Borrowed from {{bor|en|fr|gourmet}}, from {{etyl|frm|en}} {{m|frm|gourmet}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|groumet||wine broker, valet in charge of wines, servant}} from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|grommes||manservant}}, of {{etyl|gem|en}} origin, akin to {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|grom|grom, grome|boy, valet, servant}}, of unknown origin, perhaps from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|*grōma||male child, boy, youth}} from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|grōwan||to grow}}. More at {{m|en|groom}}.

